  <!-- LLD 1: PARKING LOT -->
  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <h2 id="lld1">1. Parking Lot System — Full Design</h2>

  <h3>Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Multi-floor parking lot with different slot sizes (Compact, Regular, Large)</li>
    <li>Support vehicle types: Motorcycle, Car, Truck</li>
    <li>Issue ticket on entry, calculate fee on exit</li>
    <li>Track available slots per floor</li>
    <li>Multiple entry/exit points</li>
    <li>Pricing: hourly rate based on vehicle type (Strategy pattern)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Class Diagram (Text)</h3>
  <pre><code>ParkingLot (Singleton)
├── floors: List&lt;ParkingFloor&gt;
├── entryPanels: List&lt;EntryPanel&gt;
├── exitPanels: List&lt;ExitPanel&gt;
└── pricingStrategy: PricingStrategy

ParkingFloor
├── floorNumber: int
├── slots: Map&lt;SlotType, List&lt;ParkingSlot&gt;&gt;
└── displayBoard: DisplayBoard

ParkingSlot
├── slotId: str
├── slotType: SlotType (COMPACT | REGULAR | LARGE)
├── isOccupied: bool
└── vehicle: Vehicle | None

Vehicle (abstract)
├── licensePlate: str
├── vehicleType: VehicleType
└── subclasses: Motorcycle, Car, Truck

Ticket
├── ticketId: str
├── vehicle: Vehicle
├── slot: ParkingSlot
├── entryTime: datetime
└── exitTime: datetime | None

PricingStrategy (interface)
├── HourlyPricing
├── FlatRatePricing
└── WeekendSurgePricing</code></pre>

  <h3>Key Classes</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-python">from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
from enum import Enum
from datetime import datetime
import uuid

class VehicleType(Enum):
    MOTORCYCLE = 1
    CAR = 2
    TRUCK = 3

class SlotType(Enum):
    COMPACT = 1
    REGULAR = 2
    LARGE = 3

VEHICLE_TO_SLOT = {"{"}
    VehicleType.MOTORCYCLE: SlotType.COMPACT,
    VehicleType.CAR: SlotType.REGULAR,
    VehicleType.TRUCK: SlotType.LARGE,
{"}"}

class Vehicle:
    def __init__(self, license_plate: str, vehicle_type: VehicleType):
        self.license_plate = license_plate
        self.vehicle_type = vehicle_type

class ParkingSlot:
    def __init__(self, slot_id: str, slot_type: SlotType):
        self.slot_id = slot_id
        self.slot_type = slot_type
        self.is_occupied = False
        self.vehicle = None

    def park(self, vehicle: Vehicle):
        self.vehicle = vehicle
        self.is_occupied = True

    def unpark(self):
        self.vehicle = None
        self.is_occupied = False

class PricingStrategy(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def calculate_fee(self, hours: float, vehicle_type: VehicleType) -&gt; float:
        pass

class HourlyPricing(PricingStrategy):
    RATES = {"{"}VehicleType.MOTORCYCLE: 10, VehicleType.CAR: 20, VehicleType.TRUCK: 30{"}"}

    def calculate_fee(self, hours, vehicle_type):
        import math
        return math.ceil(hours) * self.RATES[vehicle_type]

class Ticket:
    def __init__(self, vehicle: Vehicle, slot: ParkingSlot):
        self.ticket_id = str(uuid.uuid4())
        self.vehicle = vehicle
        self.slot = slot
        self.entry_time = datetime.now()
        self.exit_time = None

class ParkingFloor:
    def __init__(self, floor_number: int, slots: list):
        self.floor_number = floor_number
        self.slots = slots

    def find_available_slot(self, slot_type: SlotType):
        for slot in self.slots:
            if slot.slot_type == slot_type and not slot.is_occupied:
                return slot
        return None

class ParkingLot:
    _instance = None

    def __new__(cls):
        if cls._instance is None:
            cls._instance = super().__new__(cls)
        return cls._instance

    def __init__(self):
        self.floors = []
        self.active_tickets = {"{"}{"}"} 
        self.pricing = HourlyPricing()

    def park_vehicle(self, vehicle: Vehicle) -&gt; Ticket:
        slot_type = VEHICLE_TO_SLOT[vehicle.vehicle_type]
        for floor in self.floors:
            slot = floor.find_available_slot(slot_type)
            if slot:
                slot.park(vehicle)
                ticket = Ticket(vehicle, slot)
                self.active_tickets[ticket.ticket_id] = ticket
                return ticket
        raise Exception("No available slot")

    def unpark_vehicle(self, ticket_id: str) -&gt; float:
        ticket = self.active_tickets.pop(ticket_id)
        ticket.exit_time = datetime.now()
        ticket.slot.unpark()
        hours = (ticket.exit_time - ticket.entry_time).total_seconds() / 3600
        return self.pricing.calculate_fee(hours, ticket.vehicle.vehicle_type)</code></pre>

  <h3>Design Patterns</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Singleton:</strong> ParkingLot — single instance for the entire system</li>
    <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> PricingStrategy — swap pricing algorithms without changing core logic</li>
    <li><strong>Factory:</strong> Can add VehicleFactory for creating vehicle objects from input</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Evaluation Criteria</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Does candidate identify core entities and relationships?</li>
    <li>Is the slot assignment strategy flexible (can we add EV charging slots)?</li>
    <li>Thread safety for concurrent entry/exit?</li>
    <li>Extensibility: add new vehicle types, new pricing?</li>
  </ul>

