  <!-- LLD 2: ELEVATOR SYSTEM -->
  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <h2 id="lld2">2. Elevator System — Full Design</h2>

  <h3>Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Multiple elevators in a building with N floors</li>
    <li>External buttons (up/down per floor), internal panel (floor selection)</li>
    <li>Optimal scheduling: minimize wait time</li>
    <li>Support: IDLE, MOVING_UP, MOVING_DOWN, DOOR_OPEN states</li>
    <li>Emergency stop and overweight detection</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Class Diagram (Text)</h3>
  <pre><code>ElevatorSystem (Controller)
├── elevators: List&lt;Elevator&gt;
├── scheduler: ElevatorScheduler
└── floorRequests: Queue&lt;Request&gt;

Elevator
├── id: int
├── currentFloor: int
├── state: ElevatorState (IDLE | MOVING_UP | MOVING_DOWN | DOOR_OPEN)
├── destinationQueue: SortedSet&lt;int&gt;
└── door: Door

Request
├── floor: int
├── direction: Direction (UP | DOWN)
└── timestamp: datetime

ElevatorScheduler (interface)
├── LOOKScheduler (elevator algorithm)
├── ShortestSeekScheduler
└── ZoneBasedScheduler</code></pre>

  <h3>Key Classes</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-python">from enum import Enum
from sortedcontainers import SortedList

class Direction(Enum):
    UP = 1
    DOWN = 2

class ElevatorState(Enum):
    IDLE = 1
    MOVING_UP = 2
    MOVING_DOWN = 3
    DOOR_OPEN = 4

class Request:
    def __init__(self, floor: int, direction: Direction):
        self.floor = floor
        self.direction = direction

class Elevator:
    def __init__(self, elevator_id: int, total_floors: int):
        self.id = elevator_id
        self.current_floor = 0
        self.state = ElevatorState.IDLE
        self.up_stops = SortedList()
        self.down_stops = SortedList()

    def add_destination(self, floor: int):
        if floor &gt; self.current_floor:
            self.up_stops.add(floor)
        elif floor &lt; self.current_floor:
            self.down_stops.add(floor)

    def move(self):
        if self.state == ElevatorState.MOVING_UP:
            if self.up_stops:
                self.current_floor = self.up_stops.pop(0)
            elif self.down_stops:
                self.state = ElevatorState.MOVING_DOWN
        elif self.state == ElevatorState.MOVING_DOWN:
            if self.down_stops:
                self.current_floor = self.down_stops.pop(-1)
            elif self.up_stops:
                self.state = ElevatorState.MOVING_UP
        if not self.up_stops and not self.down_stops:
            self.state = ElevatorState.IDLE

class ElevatorScheduler:
    """LOOK algorithm: pick nearest elevator moving in same direction."""
    def assign(self, request: Request, elevators: list) -&gt; Elevator:
        best = None
        best_score = float('inf')
        for elevator in elevators:
            score = self._score(elevator, request)
            if score &lt; best_score:
                best_score = score
                best = elevator
        return best

    def _score(self, elevator: Elevator, request: Request) -&gt; int:
        distance = abs(elevator.current_floor - request.floor)
        # Prefer idle elevators, then same-direction, then others
        if elevator.state == ElevatorState.IDLE:
            return distance
        elif (elevator.state == ElevatorState.MOVING_UP and
              request.direction == Direction.UP and
              elevator.current_floor &lt;= request.floor):
            return distance
        elif (elevator.state == ElevatorState.MOVING_DOWN and
              request.direction == Direction.DOWN and
              elevator.current_floor &gt;= request.floor):
            return distance
        return distance + 100  # penalty for opposite direction

class ElevatorSystem:
    def __init__(self, num_elevators: int, num_floors: int):
        self.elevators = [Elevator(i, num_floors) for i in range(num_elevators)]
        self.scheduler = ElevatorScheduler()

    def request_elevator(self, floor: int, direction: Direction):
        request = Request(floor, direction)
        elevator = self.scheduler.assign(request, self.elevators)
        elevator.add_destination(floor)
        if elevator.state == ElevatorState.IDLE:
            if floor &gt; elevator.current_floor:
                elevator.state = ElevatorState.MOVING_UP
            else:
                elevator.state = ElevatorState.MOVING_DOWN</code></pre>

  <h3>Design Patterns</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>State:</strong> Elevator states govern behavior (IDLE, MOVING_UP, MOVING_DOWN)</li>
    <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> ElevatorScheduler — pluggable scheduling algorithms</li>
    <li><strong>Observer:</strong> Floor displays subscribe to elevator position changes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Evaluation Criteria</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Does the scheduling algorithm handle edge cases (all elevators busy)?</li>
    <li>State transitions correct (can't go from MOVING_UP to DOOR_OPEN without stopping)?</li>
    <li>Extensibility: add express elevators, VIP priority?</li>
  </ul>

