  <!-- LLD 4: PUB/SUB SYSTEM -->
  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <h2 id="lld4">4. Pub/Sub Messaging System — Full Design</h2>

  <h3>Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Publishers send messages to topics</li>
    <li>Subscribers register to topics and receive messages</li>
    <li>Support multiple subscribers per topic</li>
    <li>Message ordering within a topic</li>
    <li>At-least-once delivery guarantee</li>
    <li>Subscriber groups (only one in group receives each message)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Class Diagram (Text)</h3>
  <pre><code>MessageBroker
├── topics: Map&lt;str, Topic&gt;
├── createTopic(name) -&gt; Topic
├── publish(topicName, message) -&gt; void
└── subscribe(topicName, subscriber) -&gt; void

Topic
├── name: str
├── messages: Queue&lt;Message&gt;
├── subscribers: List&lt;Subscriber&gt;
└── publish(message) -&gt; void

Message
├── id: str
├── payload: Any
├── timestamp: datetime
└── headers: Map&lt;str, str&gt;

Subscriber (interface)
├── onMessage(message) -&gt; void
└── implementations:
    ├── PrintSubscriber
    ├── DatabaseSubscriber
    └── WebhookSubscriber</code></pre>

  <h3>Key Classes</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-python">import uuid
import threading
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
from collections import defaultdict, deque
from datetime import datetime

class Message:
    def __init__(self, payload, headers=None):
        self.id = str(uuid.uuid4())
        self.payload = payload
        self.headers = headers or {"{"}{"}"} 
        self.timestamp = datetime.now()

class Subscriber(ABC):
    def __init__(self, subscriber_id: str):
        self.id = subscriber_id

    @abstractmethod
    def on_message(self, message: Message) -&gt; None:
        pass

class PrintSubscriber(Subscriber):
    def on_message(self, message: Message):
        print(f"[{"{"}self.id{"}"}] Received: {"{"}message.payload{"}"}")

class Topic:
    def __init__(self, name: str):
        self.name = name
        self.subscribers = []
        self.messages = deque(maxlen=10000)  # retain last 10k
        self.lock = threading.Lock()

    def add_subscriber(self, subscriber: Subscriber):
        with self.lock:
            self.subscribers.append(subscriber)

    def remove_subscriber(self, subscriber_id: str):
        with self.lock:
            self.subscribers = [s for s in self.subscribers if s.id != subscriber_id]

    def publish(self, message: Message):
        with self.lock:
            self.messages.append(message)
            for subscriber in self.subscribers:
                try:
                    subscriber.on_message(message)
                except Exception as e:
                    print(f"Error delivering to {"{"}subscriber.id{"}"}: {"{"}e{"}"}")

class MessageBroker:
    def __init__(self):
        self.topics = {"{"}{"}"} 
        self.lock = threading.Lock()

    def create_topic(self, name: str) -&gt; Topic:
        with self.lock:
            if name not in self.topics:
                self.topics[name] = Topic(name)
            return self.topics[name]

    def publish(self, topic_name: str, payload) -&gt; None:
        topic = self.topics.get(topic_name)
        if not topic:
            raise ValueError(f"Topic '{"{"}topic_name{"}"}' not found")
        message = Message(payload)
        topic.publish(message)

    def subscribe(self, topic_name: str, subscriber: Subscriber) -&gt; None:
        topic = self.topics.get(topic_name)
        if not topic:
            raise ValueError(f"Topic '{"{"}topic_name{"}"}' not found")
        topic.add_subscriber(subscriber)

# Usage
broker = MessageBroker()
broker.create_topic("orders")
broker.subscribe("orders", PrintSubscriber("email-service"))
broker.subscribe("orders", PrintSubscriber("analytics"))
broker.publish("orders", {"{"}"order_id": 123, "amount": 49.99{"}"})</code></pre>

  <h3>Design Patterns</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Observer:</strong> Core pattern — Topic notifies all subscribers</li>
    <li><strong>Strategy:</strong> Delivery strategies (push vs pull, sync vs async)</li>
    <li><strong>Decorator:</strong> Add retry logic, logging around subscribers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Evaluation Criteria</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Thread safety in publish/subscribe operations</li>
    <li>Handling slow subscribers (async delivery, backpressure)</li>
    <li>Dead letter queue for failed messages</li>
    <li>Subscriber groups: load balancing messages across group members</li>
  </ul>

